title: Death Has a Shadow
description: Peter loses his job, but ends up getting rich off welfare.

title: I Never Met the Dead Man
description: After crashing into the town's TV transmitter, Peter discovers life without television.

title: Chitty Chitty Death Bang
description: Stewie has his first birthday, while Meg makes a new friend.

title: Mind Over Murder
description: Confined to house arrest, Peter opens a bar in the basement.

title: A Hero Sits Next Door
description: Peter gets jealous when the new neighbor starts stealing the spotlight.

title: The Son Also Draws
description: The Griffins head to New York in order to re-gain Chris entry back into the Boy Scouts which Chris doesn't even want to be in. But on the way the decide to stop at an Indian casino. Once there Lois loses all of the family's money and then the car.

title: Brian: Portrait of a Dog
description: Brian's life is on the line after he refuses to be treated like a dog.

title: Peter, Peter, Caviar Eater
description: Peter changes for the worse after he and Lois inherit a mansion in Newport.

title: Holy Crap
description: Peter's ultra-religious father causes trouble when he comes to live with the family.

title: Da Boom
description: The Griffins survive a Y2K atomic holocaust and attempt to rebuild civilization.

title: Brian in Love
description: Brian suffers from a mid-life crisis that may be due to unrequited love.

title: Love Thy Trophy
description: Everyone on Spooner Street becomes enemies when a trophy they all won mysteriously goes missing; Meg makes extra tips at her new job as a waitress by telling everyone she's unwed, teenage mother of Stewie.

title: Death Is a Bitch
description: In an attempt to avoid paying expensive hospital bill, Peter says that he is dead on hospital sign-out sheet. Later that night he visited by Death who has come to take him away. While chasing Peter down, Death twists his ankle and cannot fulfill his duties. So Peter must take his place.

title: The King Is Dead
description: Peter takes over Lois' production of The King and I.

title: I Am Peter, Hear Me Roar
description: After being sued for sexual harassment, Peter is forced to attend sensitivity training seminar. After failing miserably Peter is then sent to an all women's retreat. Upon returning Peter has a new personality and a new outlook upon life. Both of which are exactly like that of a woman's.

title: If I'm Dyin' I'm Lyin'
description: Peter's attempt to un-cancel a TV show gets him worshiped as a god.

title: Running Mates
description: Peter and Lois face off in a school board election.

title: A Picture Is Worth 1,000 Bucks
description: Chris' artwork gets discovered by a famous critic.

title: Fifteen Minutes of Shame
description: Meg's plan to embarrass her family backfires.

title: Road to Rhode Island
description: Brian and Stewie have to make their way across the US.

title: Let's Go to the Hop
description: Peter goes undercover to stop a toad-licking epidemic.

title: Dammit Janet
description: Stewie discovers love at the day care center.

title: There's Something About Paulie
description: Peter has to repay a mafia debt by playing babysitter for Big Fat Paulie.

title: He's Too Sexy for His Fat
description: Liposuction turns Peter beautiful, but insufferable.

title: E. Peterbus Unum
description: Peter's home becomes an independent nation and goes to war with the US.

title: The Story on Page One
description: Meg gets the lead story in her school paper, but it's not the one she wrote.

title: Wasted Talent
description: Peter becomes a master pianist as long as he's drunk.

title: Fore, Father
description: Peter becomes a golf mentor to Cleveland's son.

title: The Thin White Line
description: Brian gets a job with the police as a drug sniffing dog, but ends up getting hooked.

roles.char: Doctor and Swim Instructor in Providence Rehab Clinic

title: Brian Does Hollywood
description: Brian moves to Hollywood and becomes a porn director.

title: Mr. Griffin Goes to Washington
description: Peter becomes a tobacco lobbyist.

title: One If by Clam, Two If by Sea
description: Horace sells the Drunken Clam to a British investor, so the guys start a revolution.

title: And the Wiener Is...
description: Peter becomes jealous of Chris' very large endowment.

title: Death Lives
description: Peter dies again, and Death shows him the errors of his ways.

title: Lethal Weapons
description: Lois becomes a master martial artist, but can she control herself?

title: The Kiss Seen Around the World
description: Meg develops a crush on the local news anchor, Tom Tucker, so decides to take a internship at the news station as a junior anchor. But, much to her dismay her fellow anchor is Neil Goldman. A nerd from her school who's only goal in life is to be with Meg.

title: Mr. Saturday Knight
description: Tired of being stuck at his dead end job, Peter decides to invite his boss, Mr. Weed, over for dinner in hopes that he we'll give him a promotion. Not long after Peter gets his promotion, his boss chokes on a roll and dies. After Mr. Weed's funeral Peter and his fellow factory workers are informed that the factory is being torn down. With some persuasion from Lois, Peter then decides to fulfill his lifetime dream of being a Renaissance Fair knight.

title: A Fish Out of Water
description: Peter tries his hand at deep sea fishing.

title: Emission Impossible
description: Stewie panics when Lois and Peter think about having another kid.

title: To Love and Die in Dixie
description: The family has to move south as part of the Witness Protection Program.

title: Screwed the Pooch
description: Peter finally connects with his father-in-law, while Brian can't control his libido.

title: Peter Griffin: Husband, Father... Brother?
description: While learning about his family history, Chris discovers that one of Peter's ancestors was a black slave once owned by the Pewterschmidts.

title: Ready, Willing and Disabled
description: Peter coaches Joe to victory in the Special People's Games.

title: A Very Special Family Guy Freakin' Christmas
description: A series of setbacks shakes Lois' faith in the spirit of Christmas.

title: Brian Wallows and Peter's Swallows
description: Brian finds his true love, while Peter raises a family of birds.

title: From Method to Madness
description: Stewie becomes a stage star and Meg falls for a nudist.

title: Stuck Together, Torn Apart
description: Peter and Lois try dating other people.

title: Road to Europe
description: Brian follows Stewie to Europe, while Peter and Lois follow Kiss.

title: Family Guy Viewer Mail #1
description: Three shorts based on viewer mail. In "No Bones About It", Peter is granted three wishes by a magical Genie. The Griffins become superheroes after being exposed to toxic waste in "Super Griffins". In "Li'l Griffins", a young Peter and Quagmire set out to spend the night in a haunted house to impress a young Lois.

title: When You Wish Upon a Weinstein
description: Peter wants Chris to become Jewish so he'll grow up smart.

title: North by North Quahog
description: Peter and Lois try for a second honeymoon in Mel Gibson's hotel room.

title: Fast Times at Buddy Cianci Jr. High
description: Chris gets seduced by a homicidal teacher.

title: Blind Ambition
description: Peter's desire to become famous for something causes him to go blind.

title: Don't Make Me Over
description: After a makeover, Meg becomes an insufferable starlet.

title: The Cleveland-Loretta Quagmire
description: Cleveland's wife Loretta has an affair with Quagmire.

title: Petarded
description: After winning at the children's edition of trivial pursuit, Peter thinks he's a genius until testing proves that he's actually mentally retarded.

title: Brian the Bachelor
description: Brian appears on a dating show, while Chris takes advice from his pimple.

title: 8 Simple Rules for Buying My Teenage Daughter
description: Peter resorts to selling Meg in order to pay off his pharmacy tab.

title: Breaking Out Is Hard to Do
description: Lois goes to jail after a shoplifting crime spree.

title: Model Misbehavior
description: Lois becomes a model, but goes overboard with the glamor life.

title: Peter's Got Woods
description: Brian tries to rename James Woods High School, but Peter pulls out a surprise weapon.

title: The Perfect Castaway
description: Peter gets rescued after being lost at sea for months, but comes home to find things have changed.

title: Jungle Love
description: To avoid Freshman hazing, Chris runs away to South America to join the Peace Corp. When Peter and the family come to get him, Peter learns that he's the richest man in the tribe and goes about exploiting the tribe.

title: PTV
description: After an incident at the Emmys the FCC overreacts and begins to censor anything and everything that may be viewed as unpleasant. So Peter gets the idea to start his own cable network dedicated to all of the "smut" television once offered. Lois, naturally being uncomfortable with this contacts the FCC who then shuts Peter down. Feeling that shutting him down is not enough the FCC then decides to begin censoring life.

title: Brian Goes Back to College
description: Brian re-enrolls at Brown while Peter and the guys become the new A-Team.

title: The Courtship of Stewie's Father
description: Peter tries to bond with Stewie in a number of different ways.

title: Fat Guy Strangler
description: Lois discovers a long-lost brother, but her new relative has a deadly secret.

roles.char: Ball in a Cup Ad Singing Voice

title: The Father, the Son and the Holy Fonz
description: During one of his visits Peter's father, Francis, discovers that Stewie has never been baptized, so without Lois' permission Peter and Francis go to church and have him baptized. Upon discovering this, Lois convinces Peter that Stewie should have been able to worship whomever he wanted regardless of his father's religion. Naturally Peter interprets Lois' wisdom the wrong way so decides to start his own religious group that praises the television character, Arthur "Fonzie" Fonzarelli.

title: Brian Sings & Swings
description: Brian and Stewie go on tour singing classic tunes with Frank Sinatra, Jr.

title: Patriot Games
description: After quarterback Tom Brady witnesses Peter pummeling several people in order to get to the bathroom, he recruits him to play for the New England Patriots.

title: I Take Thee, Quagmire
description: Quagmire falls in love with and marries the Maid that Peter won on a game show only to find out that she's a psycho and must figure out a way to get out of it.

title: Sibling Rivalry
description: Peter is set to have a vasectomy against his will, but has an accident at the sperm bank, which causes Stewie's rival sibling to be born. Meanwhile, Lois gains weight after an angry Peter refuses to have sex with her anymore.

title: Deep Throats
description: While Meg interns for Mayor West, Brian uncovers a scandal; Peter and Lois decide to reunite their old groovy band

title: Peterotica
description: Peter becomes a best-selling erotica book author. But a lawsuit puts his investor--Lois's father--in the poorhouse and forces him to move in with the Griffins.

title: You May Now Kiss the... Uh... Guy Who Receives
description: Brian's gay cousin Jasper comes to town for a visit to see Brian. Jasper brings with him a man he wants to marry, but Mayor West is trying to ban gay marriage to distract everyone from a financial scandal.

title: Petergeist
description: When Joe buys a new home theater system, Peter gets jealous and decides to build a multiplex movie theater in his back yard. But while doing so, he finds a human skull. It begins haunting the Griffin house, and Stewie gets sucked through a portal into the realm of the dead.

title: Untitled Griffin Family History
description: When burglars break into the house, the Griffins take cover in the attic where they discover Peter has built a 'panic room'. They go in it, and Peter tells them about his history. They send Meg for food but the burglars catch her. The rest of the Griffins stay behind and Peter accidentally floods the room and they're going to drown. Luckily Joe gets them out and we find out Meg has been accused of sexual harassment by the burglars.

title: Stewie B. Goode
description: A near-death experience inspires Stewie to change his life.

title: Bango Was His Name, Oh!
description: Stewie searches a man he saw on TV whom he believes is his real father.

title: Stu & Stewie's Excellent Adventure
description: Stewie meets his future self, who lives a pathetic life.

title: Stewie Loves Lois
description: After Lois saves Stewie's bear, Rupert, he begins to appreciate her more than ever. But Lois soon grows tired of this attention. At the same time, Peter goes to court suing Dr. Heartman of sexual harassment.

title: Mother Tucker
description: Peter's mom starts dating TV anchor Tom Tucker, causing Peter to turn to him as the father figure he always wanted. And Brian and Stewie begin hosting their own raunchy radio program.

title: Hell Comes to Quahog
description: Meg takes a job at the local "superstore," but the store causes Peter to lose his job and his electricity. So he becomes the store's most vocal critic--until it offers him a job.

title: Saving Private Brian
description: Stewie and Brian join the army, go through basic training, and are sent to Iraq. Meanwhile, Chris becomes the lead singer of a rock band until Peter and Lois get Marilyn Manson to talk him out of it.

title: Whistle While Your Wife Works
description: Lois does Peter's work at the brewery while he recovers from getting his fingers surgically reattached, and Brian doesn't want the family to know that he's dating an idiot.

title: Prick Up Your Ears
description: Lois becomes the high school sex ed teacher, but is fired for having "radical" views. So she is replaced by a Christian group that uses fear, misinformation and lies to promote abstinence.

title: Chick Cancer
description: Stewie tries to win over a retired child actress, and Peter becomes a fan of "chick movies" and makes his own.

title: Barely Legal
description: Meg can't find a date to her junior prom and Brian ends up going with Meg.

title: Road to Rupert
description: Stewie and Brian travel to Aspen to find the man that Brian sold Rupert to on accident at a garage sale, and Meg becomes Peter's personal driver after Peter temporarily loses his driving privileges.

title: Peter's Two Dads
description: After Peter's dad passes away, he learns that he's not his biological father. So he and Brian travel to Ireland to find his real father.

title: The Tan Aquatic with Steve Zissou
description: Peter becomes the neighborhood bully after trying to take care of Chris's bully, and Stewie has a cancer scare after staying in the tanning bed too long.

title: Airport '07
description: Peter becomes a redneck and gets Quagmire fired. So the gang sets out to get Quagmire his job back.

title: Bill & Peter's Bogus Journey
description: Peter's attempts to become physically fit lead to a friendship with Bill Clinton, which inadvertently nearly destroys Peter & Lois' marriage.

title: No Meals on Wheels
description: After Peter finds a valuable coin and sells it for $50,000, he and Lois open their own restaurant. Peter is dismayed, however, when Joe and all of his handicapped friends begin using the restaurant as their hangout, and bans them all. This leads to a huge showdown and an ironic fate for Peter.

roles.char: Peter Griffin with the vocal chords of Patrick Stewart

title: Boys Do Cry
description: Lois gets a job as the church organist, so the family decides to begin going back to church. When Stewie gets sick after receiving communion, the congregation becomes convinced that he has been possessed by the devil. While on the run, the family ends up in Texas, where Peter begins to fit right in with the cowboys, Stewie enters the "Little Miss Texas" pageant, and Chris and Meg sneak into George W. Bush's house.

title: No Chris Left Behind
description: After being expelled by his school for dragging down their average standardized test scores, Chris is accepted into a snobby private school, which forces his family to struggle to pay the tuition.

title: It Takes a Village Idiot, and I Married One
description: Lois runs for mayor of Quahog, though she doesn't become the front-runner until she dumbs down her political views. Once in office, she becomes corrupted with the power that she now holds, and begins accepting bribes so that she can buy herself expensive things. Meanwhile, Peter comes to enjoy being the "first lady" of Quahog, and all of the perks that go along with it.

title: Meet the Quagmires
description: Death grants Peter's wish to go back in time to 1984 when he was 18, but only for one night. He end up bailing on a date with Lois to hang out with a movie actress. When he returns to the present, he soon realizes that everything is but normal, as he is now married to the former actress, and Lois is with Quagmire.

title: Blue Harvest
description: With the Griffins stuck at home during a blackout, Peter begins to tell a story, which leads to a Star Wars flashback. Acting out scenes from Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope.

roles.char: Bruce the Performance Artist as Greedo
Mayor Adam West as Grand Moff Tarkin

title: Movin' Out (Brian's Song)
description: Brian moves in with Jillian, but Stewie moves in too to help pay the rent. Meg and Chris both get jobs at the local convenience store.

title: Believe It or Not, Joe's Walking on Air
description: Joe has a new surgery performed on him which allows him to walk. But the new Joe then abandons all of his old friends because they're all a bunch of lazy losers.

title: Stewie Kills Lois
description: Stewie kills his mother Lois. But one year after her disappearance, Peter is charged with her death.

title: Lois Kills Stewie
description: With Lois back in Quahog, Stewie escapes with Brian to Washington, D.C. and sets out to initiate his latest plan for world domination.

title: Padre de Familia
description: Peter discovers that he is an illegal Mexican immigrant, so he is forced to take a job as a day laborer for Lois's father.

title: Peter's Daughter
description: Meg is admitted to hospital due to a severe accident, and Peter vows to treat her better than he ever has before.

title: McStroke
description: Peter sues a fast food chain after he suffers a stroke from eating over 30 hamburgers in one sitting.

title: Back to the Woods
description: James Woods gets his revenge on Peter by stealing his identity and moving in with his family. Peter responds by stealing Woods's identity and ruining his career.

title: Play It Again, Brian
description: Brian decides to declare his love for Lois as she and Peter accompany him to a writers' convention, and the Griffin kids are babysat by Herbert.

title: The Former Life of Brian
description: When Brian decides to look up an old flame on a whim, he discovers, to his horror, that he is the father of her teenage son.

title: Long John Peter
description: Peter feigns the life as a Pirate when he gets a pet Parrot. He terrorizes his neighbors and creates havoc in Quahog. When Chris takes Brian to the vet, Chris falls in love with the lovely intern Anna.

title: Love Blactually
description: Stewie convinces Brian to take it slow with his new girlfriend, but she becomes impatient and hooks up with Cleveland. Brian then tries to get Cleveland back together with his ex-wife Loretta to get him out of the picture.

title: I Dream of Jesus
description: Peter discovers that Jesus Christ is working at a used record store and Quahog, and sets out to let everyone know that he has come back.

title: Road to Germany
description: Stewie and Brian use a time machine to go back to Nazi-era Poland and rescue Mort.

title: Baby Not on Board
description: The Griffins go on vacation but accidentally leave Stewie at home.

title: The Man with Two Brians
description: Peter gets the Griffins a new, younger dog to eventually replace an aging Brian.

title: Tales of a Third Grade Nothing
description: Peter must pass the third grade in order to get a promotion at the brewery. Brian and Frank Sinatra Jr. buy the nightclub, and Stewie turns it into a trendy hotspot.

title: Ocean's Three and a Half
description: The guys try to find a way to help Joe and Bonnie get money to pay their hospital bills after their baby is born, a baby that Stewie has a crush on

title: Family Gay
description: Peter becomes temporarily gay after participating in a medical study.

title: The Juice Is Loose!
description: Everyone is up in arms after Peter becomes friends with O.J. Simpson.

title: FOX-y Lady
description: Lois gets a job as an anchor at Fox News, while Peter and Chris try to sell a cartoon pilot to the Fox network.

title: Not All Dogs Go to Heaven
description: Meg finds religion while in bed with the Mumps, and reveals to the community that Brian is an Atheist. Meanwhile, Stewie builds a transporter to bring the cast of "Star Trek: The Next Generation" to Quahog.
Brian becomes the leading proponent for legalization of marijuana in Quahog.

title: Stew-Roids
description: Stewie begins taking steroids after he is beat up by a baby girl, and Chris begins dating one of the most popular girls in the school.

title: We Love You Conrad
description: Brian dates "Hills" star Lauren Conrad while trying to hide the fact that he is in love with someone else.

title: Three Kings
description: A series of parodies based on the Stephen King movies "Stand by Me," "Misery," and "The Shawshank Redemption."

title: Peter's Progress
description: The story of Griffin Peterson and the founding of Quahog.

title: Road to the Multiverse
description: Stewie and Brian explore a series of alternate universes.

title: Family Goy
description: When Peter and Lois find out that Lois' mother was a Holocaust survivor, Peter decides that the Griffins will adopt the Jewish faith, until a vision of his dead father changes his mind.

title: Spies Reminiscent of Us
description: With the help of Chevy Chase and Dan Aykroyd, Stewie and Brian discover that mayor Adam West is a Cold War sleeper agent. Meanwhile, Peter, Quagmire, and Joe start an improv comedy group.

title: Brian's Got a Brand New Bag
description: When Brian snags an older woman, he's the laughingstock of the family, but things get really bad when she breaks her hip and Brian has to be her errand-boy.

roles.char: Deputy Police Chief Dwayne T. Robinson

title: Hannah Banana
description: Brian helps Stewie meet Miley Cyrus before her concert in Quahog, and they discover a secret about her identity. Meanwhile, the family discovers that the evil monkey in Chris's closet isn't actually evil.

title: Quagmire's Baby
description: Quagmire is forced to take care of a baby he fathered when she is left on his doorstep, while Stewie creates clones of himself and Brian.

title: Jerome Is the New Black
description: The guys find a new black friend to join their group, until Peter finds out that he slept with Lois. Meanwhile, Brian tries to find out why Quagmire hates him and tries to make amends.

title: Dog Gone
description: When Brian accidentally kills another dog he is surprised to see that no one cares so he tries to convince everyone that the life of a dog should have the same value as a human one. Meanwhile, Lois hires a maid who doesn't listen to Peter.

title: Business Guy
description: Peter takes over Pewterschmidt Industries when his father-in-law has a heart attack and goes into a coma.

title: Big Man on Hippocampus
description: The Griffins are invited to be contestants on the game show "Family Feud." After winning the game and advancing to the show's bonus round (called Fast Money), Lois puts the Griffins in prime position to win the game, but Peter bungles the opportunity when he stubbornly refuses to change his answer to the first question. Host Richard Dawson tries to remind Peter of the rules, but when Peter continues to argue and grabs Dawson, he gets pushed through a podium on the set and is knocked unconscious. At the hospital, Dr. Hartman tells Lois that Peter has amnesia. At home, Lois has to re-teach Peter everything about his life, including re-introducing him to his friends and family and menial skills such as eating, driving and sex. After the latter, Peter realizes that he enjoys sex and believes he can sleep with any woman. When Peter introduces Tiffani Amber Thiessen to Lois, she loses patience with her husband and moves herself and the rest of the family out to sort out her feelings. Quagmire learns that Lois has moved out of her house and begins to court her. Brian realizes what is about to happen and warns Peter, only to learn that Peter had regained his memory but didn't tell anybody. (Peter had regained his memory after being clubbed on the head repeatedly by his nemesis, Ernie the Giant Chicken, and had kept quiet since he enjoyed his new bachelor life so much). Peter eventually walks in on Quagmire and Lois as they are engaged in foreplay, and Peter apologizes for his recent behavior and calls on her to come home. Lois accepts, and the two leave Quagmire behind, wondering what's going on.

title: Dial Meg for Murder
description: Meg goes to prison after her boyfriend escapes from jail, and returns as a frightening, hardened sociopath.

title: Extra Large Medium
description: After they are saved after being lost in the wilderness, Stewie helps Chris muster up the courage to ask a girl with Down Syndrome out on a date, while Peter pretends to be a psychic.

title: Go, Stewie, Go!
description: Stewie poses as a girl so that he can appear on a children's show, but trouble arises when he falls for a female co-star. Meanwhile, Meg gets a new boyfriend, but Lois tries to make a move on him.

title: Peter-assment
description: Peter is sexually harassed by his unattractive female boss, but will he follow through with her advances and keep his job?

title: Brian Griffin's House of Payne
description: Brian sells his pilot for a heartwarming family drama to CBS, who then turns it into a lame, formulaic sitcom starring James Woods. Meanwhile, Meg and Chris try to hide Stewie's accidental injury they caused from their parents.

title: April in Quahog
description: Peter makes an embarrassing confession about his kids as everyone thinks the world is about to come to an end.

title: Brian & Stewie
description: In the Special 1-Hour 150th Episode Event, Brian and Stewie get locked in a bank vault where they are forced to deal with each other on a whole new level. The one-hour event also includes never-before-seen musical footage.

title: Quagmire's Dad
description: Quagmire's dad comes to Quahog and announces that he's undergoing a sex change. And when Brian returns to town after a seminar, he accidentally makes the situation even more awkward.

title: The Splendid Source
description: With Cleveland's help, Peter, Joe and Quagmire blow off a couples getaway to Maine to search for the origin of the worlds funniest dirty joke.

roles.char: Dean of the Secret Order of Dirty Joke Writers

title: Something, Something, Something, Dark Side
description: Holy ship! The Family Guy empire strikes back with another hilarious parody of your favorite sci-fi saga!

roles.char: Dr. Elmer Hartman as General Rieekan
Meg Griffin as Giant Space Slug
Bruce the Performance Artist as Captain Piett
Ernie the Giant Chicken as Boba Fett
Joe Swanson as Imperial Probe Droid

title: Partial Terms of Endearment
description: Lois agrees to become a surrogate mother for a friend who is unable to conceive a child of her own. But when the friend and her husband are killed in a car accident, Lois and Peter consider whether to terminate the pregnancy.

title: And Then There Were Fewer
description: Based on Agatha Christie's And Then There Were None, this episode sees nearly the whole of Quahog including the Griffins, Joe and Tom Tucker all invited to a party in their honour in a mysterious house. After the host is murdered, the guests must band together to try to figure out who the killer is. Yet, as more murders take place and more clues are revealed, the guests must decide who to turn into the police by morning. This episode was confirmed by Macfarlane to be a canon episode, the characters killed off in this episode have been officially terminated from the Family Guy series.

roles.char: Stuffed Bear from The Great Outdoors

title: Excellence in Broadcasting
description: Brian does a 180 on Rush Limbaugh and befriends him after he reads one of his books.

title: Welcome Back Carter
description: After Peter catches Lois' dad, Carter, having an affair, he is strong-armed into keeping a secret. But when Peter accidentally spills the beans, Lois' mom demands a divorce, and Peter is in charge of Carter's return to bachelorhood.

title: Halloween on Spooner Street
description: Peter and Joe team up to execute a series of painful and humiliating Halloween pranks on unsuspecting family, friends and neighbors. While Brian shows Stewie the ropes of trick-or-treating, Meg sets out to attend her first high school Halloween party with high hopes for the evening.

title: Baby, You Knock Me Out
description: Lois becomes a champion foxy boxer, and Peter acts as her manager.

title: Brian Writes a Bestseller
description: Feeling discouraged with the progress of his writing career, Brian decides to throw in the towel until Stewie becomes his manager and one of his books hits the bestseller list. But when the fame goes to his head, Brian gets a wake-up call from Bill Maher. Meanwhile, Lois decides that she and Peter need separate beds, a decision that leaves Peter looking for a new cuddle buddy.

title: Road to the North Pole
description: When Stewie's trip to the mall to see Santa ends on a very bad note, he and Brian decide to go up to the North Pole to teach Santa a lesson in Christmas cheer, "Stewie Griffin" style.

title: New Kidney in Town
description: Peter needs a new kidney after he destroys his own by making his own energy drink, and Chris gets to introduce President Obama at his high school after he plagiarizes Meg's poem about hope.

title: And I'm Joyce Kinney
description: Lois becomes friends with the new television anchor, only to have her reveal Lois's most embarrassing secret on the air.

title: Friends of Peter G.
description: After a public disturbance, Peter and Brian are forced to attend a 12-step meeting to help kick their drinking problems. Unable to recognize his issue, Peter gets a visit from Death, who gives him a glimpse of what life would be like with and without "Mr. Booze" in his bloodstream.

title: German Guy
description: A jealous Mr. Herbert tries to tell Chris that the elderly German puppeteer that he is hanging out with is actually a notorious Nazi war criminal.

title: The Hand That Rocks the Wheelchair
description: Meg takes care of Joe while Bonnie is away, and she develops a crush. Meanwhile, Stewie creates an evil clone who escapes the house, and he and Brian try to find and stop him.

title: Trading Places
description: Chris and Meg think their parents have it easy, and Peter and Lois beg to differ, so in order to teach them a lesson, they all trade roles. Chris goes to work at the brewery while Meg runs the house. While things start off well, it's not long until the stress of running a household and being the sole breadwinner break down Chris and Meg.

title: Tiegs for Two
description: When the local dry cleaner loses Peter's favorite white shirt, he goes ballistic. Meanwhile, Brian tries to score on a date with a new friend, Denise, but ends up striking out. Instead of calling it quits on love, he decides to enlist Quagmire's help, but things get nasty when they start to compete for the affections of each other's old flames, Cheryl Tiegs and Jillian.

title: Brothers & Sisters
description: Lois's sister comes to town after yet another failed marriage, and quickly becomes engaged to mayor Adam West.

title: The Big Bang Theory
description: Stewie and Brian go back in time to stop Bertram from killing Leonardo da Vinci.

title: Foreign Affairs
description: Lois goes on a vacation with Bonnie to Paris, not knowing that Bonnie's intentions are to cheat on Joe. Back at home, Peter decides to homeschool the kids.

title: Episode VI: It's a Trap
description: Clear some space for the third chapter of the funniest freakin' trilogy in the galaxy!

roles.char: Joe Swanson as Jabba the Hutt
Mayor Adam West as Grand Moff Tarkin

title: Lottery Fever
description: Peter blows his savings on lottery tickets and the family writes it off as one of his usual shenanigans until they end up millionaires. In true Griffin fashion, they can't handle the good fortune and struggle to stay grounded.

roles.char: A Checkout Girl in a Cheap Dress Who Wants to Be a Model

title: Seahorse Seashell Party
description: As a hurricane hits Quahog, Brian gets high on psychedelic mushrooms and cuts his ear off, and Meg finally summons up the courage to confront the family.

title: Screams of Silence: The Story of Brenda Q
description: Quagmire and his friends try to talk his sister into getting away from her abusive boyfriend. But when she won't listen, they decide to take matters into their own hands.

title: Stewie Goes for a Drive
description: Peter befriends actor Ryan Reynolds until he discovers that Reynolds may be attracted to him, and Stewie leaves home after Brian figures out that he wrecked Brian's car.

title: Back to the Pilot
description: Brian and Stewie travel back in time to January 31, 1999 and witness the events that took place in the very first episode of Family Guy, "Death Has a Shadow".

title: Thanksgiving
description: Joe's son, who was reported missing in Iraq, suddenly and unexpectedly appears during Thanksgiving dinner, but the story of his disappearance doesn't add up.

title: Amish Guy
description: The Griffins stay in an Amish village after their car breaks down, but problems arise when Meg falls for a boy in the village.

roles.char: Legs Go All The Way Up Griffin

title: Cool Hand Peter
description: Peter and the guys take a stand against their wives and flee to the Deep South on a road trip. On the way there, the men earn a one-way ticket to jail. But when they decide to make a run for it, Joe's quick planning and Peter's seductive ways help them escape. Meanwhile, Lois spends some quality time with the girls and they engage in childish antics.

title: Grumpy Old Man
description: Lois's dad retires to a senior community in Florida, but has trouble getting used to it.

title: Meg and Quagmire
description: When Meg turns 18, Quagmire tries to make his move on her, but Peter tries to stop him.

title: The Blind Side
description: Brian discovers that his new blind girlfriend can't stand dogs, and Peter cannot negotiate his way down the new staircase.

title: Livin' on a Prayer
description: When Lois discovers that Stewie's sick playmate is being denied medical treatment because his parents are Christian Scientists, she decides to take matters into her own hands.

title: Tom Tucker: The Man and His Dream
description: Tom Tucker goes to Hollywood to revive his acting career, with Peter as his agent. Back in Quahog, Chris starts dating a girl who looks exactly like Lois.

title: Be Careful What You Fish For
description: Peter allows a friendly dolphin to move in with the family, but soon discovers that he's really a jerk. Meanwhile, Stewie asks for Brian's help in busting a negligent day care provider.

title: Burning Down the Bayit
description: Overwhelmed with financial troubles, Mort asks Peter and Quagmire to help him save his pharmacy. However, things take a turn for the worse when the trio decides to burn it down to collect insurance money.

title: Killer Queen
description: When Peter and Chris go away to fat camp, they cross paths with a serial killer who targets overweight kids. Meanwhile, Stewie is traumatized by the frightening cover of a Queen album.

title: Forget-Me-Not
description: After a car accident, Peter, Brian, Joe, and Quagmire wake up in a hospital with no memory and discover that they're the last people left on Earth.

title: You Can't Do That on Television, Peter
description: Peter creates his own children's TV show and portrays Lois as an annoying nag, while Meg gets a chance to shadow a doctor.

title: Mr. & Mrs. Stewie
description: Stewie falls for a girl who is just as wicked as he is, and Peter finds an unlikely alternative when Lois refuses to snuggle.

title: Leggo My Meg-O
description: Meg and her friend are kidnapped in Paris for the sex slave trade, and Stewie and Brian fly to Paris to rescue her.

title: Tea Peter
description: Peter joins the Tea Party but doesn't discover until it's too late that Carter Pewterschmidt is using the party to get rid of government for his own selfish motives.

title: Viewer Mail #2
description: Three skits: the British program that Family Guy is based on, everybody Peter touches turns into Robin Williams, and a look at the day through Stewie's eyes.

title: Internal Affairs
description: Peter talks Joe into having an affair and gets into another epic fight with the giant chicken.

title: Into Fat Air
description: The Griffins try to beat Lois's obnoxious ex-boyfriend's family to the top of Mount Everest.

title: Ratings Guy
description: After the Griffins become a Nielsen Family, everyone gets mad at Peter for convincing the networks to make ridiculous changes to popular shows.

title: The Old Man and the Big 'C'
description: Brian discovers that Carter Pewterschmidt is dying of cancer, but soon becomes suspicious when he makes a seemingly impossible and miraculous recovery.

title: Yug Ylimaf
description: Brian causes time to move backwards when he tampers with Stewie's time machine, which may result in Stewie being unborn.

title: Joe's Revenge
description: Joe, with the help of Peter and Quagmire, looks to track down the person responsible for Joe's injuries.

title: Lois Comes Out of Her Shell
description: While Lois goes through a mid-life crisis, Stewie discovers that his new pet turtle is evil.

title: Friends Without Benefits
description: Meg finds out that her crush is actually gay and is interested in Chris.

title: Jesus, Mary and Joseph!
description: The Griffins decorate their tree while Peter tells the story of Christmas.

roles.char: Bruce the Performance Artist as Angel Gabriel

title: Space Cadet
description: The Griffins wind up stuck in orbit on a space shuttle after Peter and Lois send Chris to Florida for space camp.

title: Brian's Play
description: Brian receives widespread acclaim for his new play, but how will he react when Stewie writes a play overnight that puts his to shame?

title: The Giggity Wife
description: After a drunken night out at Harvard with the guys, Quagmire discovers that he married a decrepit old prostitute.

title: Valentine's Day in Quahog
description: Quahog is love-ly.

title: Chris Cross
description: Chris is fed up with Meg's efforts to blackmail him, so he moves in with Mr. Herbert. Meanwhile, Stewie and Brian became huge fans of 70s soft rock star Anne Murray.

title: Call Girl
description: Lois works for a phone sex line and Peter falls in love with her, not knowing that he is actually speaking to his wife.

title: Turban Cowboy
description: Peter becomes a Muslim but later discovers that he is also part of a terrorist plot to blow up a bridge in Quahog.

title: 12 and a Half Angry Men
description: Mayor West is on trial for murder, and Brian is the only one on the jury who thinks he is not guilty.

title: Bigfat
description: Peter reverts back to a feral state after being lost in the Canadian wilderness for two months after a plane crash.

title: Total Recall
description: Lois begins hanging out with Joe and Quagmire while Peter is sick, and Stewie tries to rescue Rupert after he is recalled.

title: Save the Clam
description: The guys fight to save The Drunken Clam after the bank closes it, and Meg gets into trouble at her new job at the funeral home.

title: Farmer Guy
description: Peter and the whole family move to a farm because of the higher crime rate in quahog. Sooner or later the family discovers a meth lab in the basement.

title: Roads to Vegas
description: Stewie uses his untested teleportation device to transport Brian and himself to Vegas. The machine creates an exact copy of the pair and sends the copy to Vegas.

title: No Country Club for Old Men
description: It's Vegas and golf, baby. Download part 2 now!

title: Finders Keepers
description: Peter goes on a real-life treasure hunt based on a treasure map from a child's meal menu.

title: Vestigial Peter
description: Peter has a vestigial twin growing of his neck, and he has surgery to remove it and have it become a separate entity.

title: Quagmire's Quagmire
description: Quagmire falls in love with a woman who is just as kinky as he is, but doesn't find out until it's too late that she's a complete psycho.

title: A Fistful of Meg
description: Meg turns to Quagmire for help taking on a school bully, and Brian looks for a way to get back at Peter for forcing him to see him naked.

title: Boopa-dee Bappa-dee
description: The Griffins take a trip to Italy and are forced to deal with annoying immigration laws after Peter destroys the family's passports.

title: Life of Brian
description: Brian dies and Stewie cannot use his time machine to save him. Meanwhile, Peter replaces Brian with an Italian dog named Vinny.

title: Into Harmony's Way
description: Fame gets to Peter when he forms a song writing team with Quagmire.

title: Christmas Guy
description: Peter fills Carter with the spirit of Christmas; Stewie goes on to get the only thing he wants for Christmas.

title: Peter Problems
description: Lately Peter hasn't been able to perform very well in the bedroom. So he asks Quagmire and Joe to step in and help him get his mojo back.

title: Grimm Job
description: Peter tells Stewie the stories "Jack and the Beanstalk," "Little Red Riding Hood," and "Cinderella."

title: Brian's a Bad Father
description: Brian uses his son to get a writing job for a TV show, and Quagmire stops being friends with Peter after Peter shoots him.

title: Mom's the Word
description: Peter is seduced by his late mother's longtime friend, while Stewie is distraught over the realities of death.

title: 3 Acts of God
description: Peter is sick of opposing football teams thanking God for beating the Patriots, so he and the guys go on a quest to find the Lord and ask Him to stop interfering in the outcomes of football games.

title: Fresh Heir
description: When Chris is made the sole heir to Carter's fortune, he refuses to take the money, so Peter takes drastic measures to keep the wealth in the family.

title: Secondhand Spoke
description: Peter is asked to be the face of an anti-smoking campaign after taking up smoking cigarettes, while Stewie helps Chris face school bullies.

title: Herpe, the Love Sore
description: Stewie gets herpes from Brian, while Peter and the guys discover that another group has taken their favorite booth at the Drunken Clam.

title: The Most Interesting Man in the World
description: Lois calls Peter an idiot for bringing home the wrong baby after he takes Stewie to the park for some father-son bonding, so he goes to Chicago on a business trip and returns a smart, classy person.

title: Baby Got Black
description: Chris runs away with Jerome's daughter Pam, whom Jerome has forbidden Chris from dating, so Jerome must work with Peter to find their kids.

title: Meg Stinks!
description: Peter takes Meg to a college for an interview where they end up partying, while Brian is forced to live in the wild after a skunk sprays him.

title: He's Bla-ack!
description: Cleveland returns to Quahog, but is forbidden from spending time with Peter when their wives get into an argument over parenting.

title: Chap Stewie
description: Stewie tries to erase himself from history when Peter and Chris constantly interrupt his TV time, only to end up as the baby of a British family.

title: The Simpsons Guy
description: The Griffins end up in Springfield while on a road trip and meet the Simpsons.

title: Family Guy Presents: Seth & Alex's Almost Live Comedy Show
